# Trim the build context sent to the Docker daemon. The Backstage
# Dockerfile needs the repo root to resolve Yarn workspaces — without
# this file we ship ~2 GiB of node_modules + cargo target to the daemon
# on every build, which is an order of magnitude slowdown.

# Node
**/node_modules/
**/dist/
**/dist-types/
**/coverage/

# Yarn
.yarn/cache/
.yarn/install-state.gz
.yarn/unplugged/
.yarn/build-state.yml

# Rust
native/target/

# Go build outputs (binaries land next to cmd/ by default)
engine/engine
cli/rampart
integrations/*/mock-npm-registry
integrations/*/slack-notifier
integrations/*/rampart-precommit

# Tooling artefacts
*.log
*.tsbuildinfo
.DS_Store
.git/

# Test harnesses
e2e/test-results/
e2e/playwright-report/
e2e/blob-report/

# Unit + integration test artefacts — none of these need to ride into
# the Docker build context. The Dockerfile never touches them, but
# COPYing backstage/plugins/**/* wholesale otherwise drags them along.
**/__tests__/
**/__mocks__/
**/*.test.ts
**/*.test.tsx
**/*.test.js
**/*.spec.ts
**/*.spec.tsx
**/*.spec.js
**/jest.config.*
**/jest.setup.*

# Storybook — dev-only surface, zero runtime relevance.
**/.storybook/
**/*.stories.ts
**/*.stories.tsx

# Generated source maps live next to dist/ entries and cost ~7 MiB
# of frontend bundle weight with zero runtime use. Keep them in git
# for local debug; exclude from the Docker build context.
**/*.map

# Markdown + changelogs — Backstage plugins ship per-package README
# and CHANGELOG files that the runtime doesn't read.
**/CHANGELOG.md
**/*.md

# Local generated fixtures (huge benchmark lockfiles, seeded on demand)
engine/testdata/lockfiles/medium-*-pkgs.json
engine/testdata/lockfiles/large-*-pkgs.json
engine/testdata/lockfiles/huge-*-pkgs.json

# Editor / OS
.vscode/
!.vscode/extensions.json
.idea/
